Pre-heat your #oven{} to 220 degrees. Peel and chop your @Swede{2} in half, then chop into chip
shaped pieces roughly the length of your index finger and 1cm wide. Grate your @Parmesan Cheese{4}, pull
your @Rosemary{5} leaves off their stalks and roughly chop them.

Add your swede chips to a #baking tray{}, drizzle over @oil{4%tbsp} and sprinkle over @salt{1/2%tsp}, a good
grind of @pepper{} and half your rosemary. Give the tray a good shake and then put in the oven on the
top shelf to cook for ~{20%minutes}.

When 20 mins are up, take your swede tray out of the oven, turn the swede chips over, add your Parmesan
to the baking tray and give it all a good shake. Pop back into the oven on the top shelf to cook
for another ~{10-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, you can tackle your sausages. Pop your @Pork and Oregano Sausage{8} onto another baking tray,
prick them each a couple of times with a sharp #knife{} or #fork{} and put them in the oven on the
second shelf to cook for ~{30%minutes}, turning halfway through.

In the meantime, you can prepare your veggies and make your red onion relish. Chop your @Red Onion{2} in
half through the root, peel and slice thinly into half moon shapes. Peel and finely chop your
@Garlic Clove{2} and cut your @Tenderstem® Broccoli{2} in half widthways.

  Heat @olive oil{3%tbsp} on low heat in a non-stick #saucepan{}. Add in the red onion slices with
@?sugar{1/2%tsp} and a pinch of salt and pepper. Cook slowly for ~{10%minutes}, stirring occasionally
and then add your @Balsamic Vinegar{2} and continue cooking slowly for another ~{10-15%minutes}.
When the onions are looking lovely and caramelised, put a #lid{} on the pan and leave to the side
until everything else is ready.

About 7 mins before everything is ready, add @oil{2%tbsp} to a #frying pan{} on medium heat and add
your broccoli and the rest of your chopped rosemary. Stir-fry for ~{5%minutes} before adding the
garlic and stir-frying for a further ~{1%minute}.

Serve your sausages with your swede chips, stir-fried broccoli and your red onion relish on the side.
Enjoy!